-shifters-draw-continuous-quiescent-current-unlike-passive-bss138-shifters-with-near-zero-idle-draw","target":"active-level-shifters-draw-continuous-quiescent-current-unlike-passive-bss138-shifters-with-near-zero-idle-draw","line":35},{"title":"active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling","target":"active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling","line":36},{"title":"txs0108e-vcca-must-be-the-lower-voltage-rail-because-the-chip-enforces-asymmetric-supply-roles","target":"txs0108e-vcca-must-be-the-lower-voltage-rail-because-the-chip-enforces-asymmetric-supply-roles","line":37},{"title":"i2s-timing-requirements-make-level-shifting-a-non-solution-for-voltage-incompatible-mcus","target":"i2s-timing-requirements-make-level-shifting-a-non-solution-for-voltage-incompatible-mcus","line":38},{"title":"mixed-protocol-boards-require-one-level-shifter-per-signal-class-not-one-shifter-for-all-signals","target":"mixed-protocol-boards-require-one-level-shifter-per-signal-class-not-one-shifter-for-all-signals","line":39},{"title":"open-drain-protocols-require-pull-up-based-level-shifters-because-auto-direction-sensors-cannot-distinguish-driver-from-pull-up","target":"open-drain-protocols-require-pull-up-based-level-shifters-because-auto-direction-sensors-cannot-distinguish-driver-from-pull-up","line":40},{"title":"logic-level-selector-switch-on-a-shield-lets-one-board-work-with-both-3v3-and-5v-arduinos-but-misconfigured-switch-produces-silent-data-corruption","target":"logic-level-selector-switch-on-a-shield-lets-one-board-work-with-both-3v3-and-5v-arduinos-but-misconfigured-switch-produces-silent-data-corruption","line":41},{"title":"every-digital-ic-requires-a-100nf-ceramic-decoupling-capacitor-between-vcc-and-gnd-to-absorb-switching-transients","target":"every-digital-ic-requires-a-100nf-ceramic-decoupling-capacitor-between-vcc-and-gnd-to-absorb-switching-trans